      <bioghist id="aspace_ed122d9d619f7bc3905faf06045d1794">
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         <p>American freelance journalist and writer (1986-present). Born 1946. Formerly deputy
            director of <title type="simple" render="italic">Viva</title> magazine; affiliated with
               <title type="simple" render="italic">US</title> and <title type="simple"
               render="italic">Newsweek.</title> Winner of the O. Henry Award.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_cd6385201c6beae145d9623cca654079">
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         <p>Collection (Accession 2002-0120) (21 items, 2.4 lin. ft.; dated 1987-2001) comprises
            primarily page and galley proofs, as well as typescripts for six of Shreve's novels and
            nonfiction books (1987-2001). The books include <title type="simple" render="italic">The
               Last Time They Met,</title>
            <title type="simple" render="italic">Fortune's Rocks, </title>
            <title type="simple" render="italic">Strange Fits of Passion, </title>
            <title type="simple" render="italic">The Weight of Water, </title>
            <title type="simple" render="italic">Remaking Motherhood, </title>and <title
               type="simple" render="italic">Resistance.</title>
         </p>
         <p>Addition (Accession 2002-0136) (300 items; 10.80 lin. ft.; dated [ca. 1989]-2002)
            consists primarily of typescript and hand-written drafts, proofs, hand-written notes,
            and research for novels by Shreve ([ca. 1989]-2002), including <title type="simple"
               render="italic">Fortune's Rocks, </title>
            <title type="simple" render="italic">The Pilot's Wife, </title>
            <title type="simple" render="italic">Sea Glass, </title>and <title type="simple"
               render="italic">The Weight of Water.</title> Addition also includes editor and
            publisher correspondence, contracts, and royalty statements (1992-1993). </p>
         <p>Addition (Accession 2003-0222) (3 items; 0.6 lin. ft.; dated 2002-2003) consists of the
            typescript (with editing marks) and master proof of Shreve's novel <title type="simple"
               render="italic">All He Ever Wanted</title> (2003), along with a piece of
            correspondence from the publisher.</p>
         <p>Addition (Accession 2011-0059) (400 items; 0.6 lin. ft.; dated 1982-1995) contains files
            about Shreve kept by Virginia Barber, her literary agent. Includes correspondence
            between them as well as Barber's correspondence and other materials promoting Shreve's
            work.</p>
      </scopecontent>
